  "prompt": "How do I know who is following me on Snapchat?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, Snapchat does not provide a direct feature that allows you to see who is following you or who has added you as a friend. However, there are a few ways you can infer this information:\n\n1. **Snapchat Friends List**: If someone has added you as a friend, they will appear in your friends list. You can access your friends list by swiping down from the camera screen and then tapping \"My Friends.\"\n\n2. **Stories Views**: When you post a story, you can see who has viewed it. If someone consistently views your stories, it is likely that they are following you.\n\n3. **Snap Score**: If you are able to see someone's Snap Score (the total number of snaps they have sent and received), it means they have added you back.\n\n4. **Snap Streaks**: If you have a Snap Streak with someone, it indicates that both of you are regularly sending snaps to each other, implying mutual following.\n\n5. **Privacy Settings**: You can check your privacy settings to see who can send you snaps and view your stories. If you have set it to \"Friends,\" then only people who have added you can interact with your content.\n\nRemember, Snapchat's features and policies may change, so it's always a good idea to check the latest updates or the Snapchat support website for the most current information.",
